Navigate
========

Allows you to identify navigation namespaces in your controllers, and
render navigation items in your views.


Basic Example
=============

In your controller:

	class PagesController < ApplicationController
		navigate :main_menu, :pages
	end

	class PostsController < ApplicationController
  	navigate :main_menu, :posts
	end
	
In your view:

  <% navigate :main_menu, :pages do %>
    <%= link_to 'Pages', pages_path %>
  <% end %>

  <% navigate :main_menu, :posts do %>
  	<%= link_to 'Users', users_path %>
  <% end %>

Assuming the request routed to the PagesController:

	<li class="selected">
		<a href="/pages">Pages</a>
	</li>
	
	<li>
		<a href="/posts">Posts</a>
	</li>
	

Navigate Independently
======================

Controller actions can navigate independently of each other:

	class PostsController
		navigate :sub_menu, :show, :only => :show
		navigate :sub_menu, :edit, :only => :edit
	end
	

Conditional Rendering
=====================

In your view, you can choose when to render a tab:

  <% navigate :main_menu, :users, :unless => !authorized? do %>
	  <%= link_to 'Users', users_path %>
	<% end %>
	

